com.github.mrgoro.interactivedata.api.handler

Class ChartRequestHandler<T extends AbstractChartDefinition<?,D>,D extends ChartData>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mrgoro.interactivedata.api.handler.ChartRequestHandler<T,D>
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    LineChartRequestHandler, PieChartRequestHandler

    @ChartRequestHandlerService
 @Named
public abstract class ChartRequestHandler<T extends AbstractChartDefinition<?,D>,D extends ChartData>
extends java.lang.Object
    Basic Implementation of a RequestHandler that is able to process a request for a specific chart.

    Abstract implementation that solves basic functionality. Should be extended for specialized purpose. Every type of chart (ChartDefinition) must have a corresponding RequestHandler.

    Every RequestHandler must at least override the convert method to support its special conversion from generic data to the specific ChartData.

    Author:
    Philipp Schürmann

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        public void initialize(T chartDefinition)
        Initialize a ChartRequestHandler with the information specified by the appropriate ChartDefinition.

        This will initialize Operation.Builder for quick creating of DataRequests with Filters, Granularities and Functions populated with the parameters from the request.

        This will also instantiate the DataSource with the class provided in the AbstractChartDefinition using the ServiceProvider.

        Parameters:
        chartDefinition - ChartDefinition containing all information about the chart this RequestHandler should handle

      • convertData

        protected abstract D convertData(java.util.List<DataObject> chartData)
        Convert generic DataObjects into the specific ChartData used for the chart type.

        As this method is abstract extending classes always have to provide an implementation of the method. The Implementation has to transform the generic data to the type used for the chart type.

        Parameters:
        chartData - Generic data queried from DataSource
        Returns:
        ChartData for the specific chart type
